"{\"uid\": \"www.tikkun.org.-nextgen-the-real-meaning-of-brexit\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"decades; a few days ago the police were exhausted from the street battles they asked protesters to give them a break.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some already speak of the \\\"second French Revolution.\\\"\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Sunday, Spaniards will elect a new government; there is a realistic chance the new president will be Pablo Iglesias, the young charismatic political science professor from Madrid leading a creative grassroots movement called \\\"Podemos,\\\" which emerged from the 2011 Indignado protests all over the country.\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 480, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Podemos is an anti-capitalist party; their number one goal is to take down the austerity regime in Spain and across Europe.\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, there is the ticking time bomb of the Greek debt crisis, there is a looming global financial meltdown, there is a refugee crisis, which we have not solved but just sealed from our attention.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore we have ecological crises of planetary dimension with existential threats to our survival\\u2026 Brexit is just a tiny puzzle piece in a much larger process of entropy taking place all over the world - the systems of society, politics, economy, but also of culture and people's coexistence are bound to disintegrate because they have produced crises that have corroded social cohesion and destroyed our basis of life on this planet.\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 1248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We live in the beginning phase of a global revolution which will turn societal conditions upside down.\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We cannot stop this transformation, but we can influence where 